-- Hungary’s OTP Rises Most in Week Lifting BUX as PMI Improves
-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 2012-01-02T09:16:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-02/hungary-s-otp-rises-most-in-week-lifting-bux-as-pmi-improves.html
OTP Bank Nyrt. (OTP) , Hungary’s largest
lender, rose the most in more than a week after a gauge of
business confidence improved.  The shares jumped 1.5 percent to 3,265 forint, the biggest
intrday advance since Dec. 23, after plunging 36 percent last
year. The benchmark BUX  index (BUX) , in which OTP has a 27 percent
weighting, rose 0.6 percent to 17,082.60.  The purchasing managers’ index rose to 48.5 points in
December from 47.8 points the previous month, the Logistics,
Purchasing and Inventory Society known as MLBKT said in a report
today. Financial markets from  Japan  to the U.K. and the U.S. are
closed for a holiday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest at 
